1-A Demonstration

library("scatterplot3d")
scatterplot3d(x=dt_Xtrain[2,],y=dt_Ytrain[2,],z=dt_Ztrain[2,],angle = 75)

#transform data to columnwise
library (data.table)
train_data<-matrix(0,nrow=896,ncol = 946)
test_data<-matrix(0,nrow=3582,ncol = 946)
train_data[,1]<-dt_Xtrain[,1]
test_data[,1]<-dt_Xtest[,1]
j<-2
for (i in 2:316)
{
  train_data[,j:(j+2)]<-cbind(dt_Xtrain[,i],dt_Ytrain[,i],dt_Ztrain[,i])
  test_data[,j:(j+2)]<-cbind(dt_Xtest[,i],dt_Ytest[,i],dt_Ztest[,i])
  j<-j+3
}

train_data<-as.data.table(train_data)
test_data<-as.data.table(test_data)
train_data$V1 = as.factor(train_data$V1)
test_data$V1 = as.factor(test_data$V1)

library(caret)
#Cross Validation properties
cv = trainControl(method = "cv",
                 number = 10,
                 ##repeats = 1,
                 classProbs = TRUE,
                 summaryFunction = multiClassSummary)

levels(train_data$V1) <- make.names(levels(factor(train_data$V1)))

levels(test_data$V1) <- make.names(levels(factor(test_data$V1)))

#training model
trainingmodel <- train(V1~. , data = train_data, method = "knn",
               preProcess = c("center","scale"),
               trControl = cv,
               ##metric = "classProbs",
               tuneLength = 5)

plot(trainingmodel)

Task 2

library(lqa)
trainECG<- read.table("~/Documents/Dersler/Fall-2018/IE-582/Homework3/NN_Classification_ecgTRAIN.dms")
testECG<-  read.table("~/Documents/Dersler/Fall-2018/IE-582/Homework3/NN_Classification_ecgTEST.dms")

# binary encode 
for (k in 1:100)
{
  if(trainECG[k,1]==-1) {
    trainECG[k,1] = 0 } 
  else
  {
    trainECG[k,1] = 1
  }
  
  if(testECG[k,1]==-1) {
    testECG[k,1] = 0 } 
  else
  {
    testECG[k,1] = 1
  }
  
}


y_train<-trainECG[,1]
x_train<-trainECG[,2:97]
y_test<-testECG[,1]
x_test<-testECG[,2:97]


optprmodel<-cv.lqa(y_train,x_train,family=binomial(),intercept = FALSE, penalty.family=fused.lasso,n.fold=10,loss.func = "aic.loss",lambda.candidates =  list (c (0.001, 0.05, 1, 5, 10), c (0.1, 0.5, 1,5)))


predictECG<-predict.lqa (optprmodel$best.obj, new.x =x_test )
a<-round(predictECG$mu.new)
a<-unname(a)

#confusionmatrix
confusionMatrix(factor(a), factor(y_test))

Task 2-C

testnew<-matrix(0,nrow=100,ncol = 96)
trainnew<-matrix(0,nrow=100,ncol = 96)

#create new data set
for (k in 1:100)
 {
  for (l in 3:96) {
    
    trainnew[k,l]=trainECG[k,l]-trainECG[k,(l-1)]
    testnew[k,l]=testECG[k,l]-testECG[k,(l-1)]
  }
  
}

x_trainew<-trainnew[,3:96]
x_testnew<-testnew[,3:96]

optprmodel2<-cv.lqa(y_train,x_trainew,family=binomial(),intercept = FALSE, penalty.family=fused.lasso,n.fold=10,loss.func = "aic.loss",lambda.candidates =  list (c (0.001, 0.05, 1, 5), c (0.1, 0.5, 1)))



predictECG<-predict.lqa (optprmodel2$best.obj, new.x =x_testnew )
predictedvalue<-round(predictECG$mu.new)
predictedvalue<-unname(predictedvalue)

#confusionmatrix
confusionMatrix(factor(predictedvalue), factor(y_test))
